
Overview of noun idol

The noun idol has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (2) idol, graven image, god -- (a material effigy that is worshipped; "thou shalt not make unto thee any graven image"; "money was his god")
2. (1) idol, matinee idol -- (someone who is adored blindly and excessively)
3. paragon, idol, perfection, beau ideal -- (an ideal instance; a perfect embodiment of a concept)
